\begin_layout Section
The USGS spectral library
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Researchers at the USGS Spectroscopy Lab have measured the spectral reflectance
 of hundreds of materials in the lab, and have compiled a spectral library.
 The libraries are used as references for material identification in remote
 sensing images.
 The website of the USGS Spectroscopy lab is 
\begin_inset Flex URL
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

http://speclab.cr.usgs.gov/
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The UV to mid-infrared 0.2-150 micron library (splib06) contains over 1300
 spectra including mid-infrared data as well as spectra from splib05a and
 additional visible and near-infrared spectra.
 The library includes many more minerals, organic and volatile compounds,
 vegetation, and man-made materials than our previous libraries.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The full USGS Spectral library is included with the Synthesis package, but
 the most recent library is always available throught the USGS Spectroscopy
 lab: 
\begin_inset Flex URL
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

http://speclab.cr.usgs.gov/spectral-lib.html
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A selection of 20 minerals endmembers is included with the Synthesis package
 as a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

endmembers_samples.mat
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 file for direct use.
 This file, localized in the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

endmembers
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 folder, loads 20 matrix each correponding to a mineral endmember (Figure
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:matlab_usgs"

\end_inset

).
 Each matrix has 
\begin_inset Formula $2151$
\end_inset

 rows and 
\begin_inset Formula $3$
\end_inset

 columns, being each row a measure for each wavelenght and the columns the
 following respectively measures: the wavelength value, the reflectance
 and the variance observed in the measuring proccess.
 reflectance is the relevant value to work in the synthetic proccess (the
 second column).
 Note that 
\begin_inset Formula $-1.23\exp^{34}$
\end_inset

 indicates a deleted number, and that standard deviations of 
\begin_inset Formula $0.000000$
\end_inset

 means not measured.
\end_layout

